  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 400°F (205°C).",
    "Mix all-purpose flour with paprika and seasonings. Coat fish fillets thoroughly in the seasoned flour.",
    "Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add garlic and cook until fragrant, about 1 minute.",
    "Add fish to the skillet and fry on both sides for approximately 5 minutes each side or until golden brown.",
    "Remove from heat and let rest for 2-3 minutes before serving with a drizzle of dijon mustard on top."
